5:
Hey, everyone. What are you all up
to?
9:
Oh, hey, Trista. We're working out our
plans for the New Year! We were
thinking about going to Yamato...
13:
Spending New Year's in Yamato...
Does this mean you're thinking of
doing hatsumode?
20:
Yes. It refers to the first visit to a
place of worship in the new year,
done as a greeting to the gods—or
kami as they're called. Did you know
there are over eight million of—
23:
W-wow, you're really knowledgeable
about this, huh?
27:
Of course! I've read—or at least
leafed through—every single book in
the Starview Village library on the
topic of Yamato!
30:
I really love everything about that
place. It's so... refined, yet strangely
melancholic...
34:
Well then, I guess it's settled! We're
going to Yamato, together!
37:
Indeed. Given that we are outsiders
unfamiliar with the local culture,
having your guidance will be most
helpful, Trista.
49:
Look at all the people who have
gathered... This tradition really IS
important to the people of Yamato.
53:
O-oh, I'm sorry, do you think I
overdid it? I was so excited about
this that I decided to put on a
kimono! I hope I don't stand out too
much...
61:
Yeah, everyone can tell how much
effort you put into it! It looks great on
you.
66:
Oh, I didn't mean to fish for
compliments like that... but thank
you!
69:
I really love wearing clothes like this.
I even got this beautiful matching
parasol! The craftsmanship on it is
incredible...
78:
Oh, I'm sorry... It's just...
The torii is a gate that leads into the
realm of the kami. You're usually
supposed to bow before you pass
through one.
81:
Oh, right... I remember hearing that
somewhere before...
85:
In that case, we'd do best to observe
the proper etiquette!
90:
Oh, no, it's actually not that strict of
a rule or anything... Lots of locals
don't do it either.
92:
Everyone has a different way of
showing their respect to the kami.
It's just important not to do anything
that disturbs other visitors!
96:
Or... that's what the books I read
said, anyway. I guess I just wanted
to actually try doing it all for myself!
100:
Well, we all want to try as well, so
don't skimp on the details!
104:
O-okay! Of course! Then, well, first
we should go over what the torii are,
exactly—
109:
Hahah! Come on, gramps... *hic*
One drink won't kill you! This stuff is
seriously the best!
111:
I'm going to have to ask you to calm
down, sir. You're inconveniencing
the other visitors.
114:
Uh-oh. Someone's had a bit too
much to drink, it looks like.
118:
New Year celebrations often bring
out this side of people. I wish they
would act with a little more restraint.
121:
Heh-heh... Well, don't you look stylish
there, little missie!
122:
How about it? You down for a drink
with yours truly? A few cups of this
stuff and you'll be talkin' with the
kami directly, heh.
125:
I, uh, no thank you...
Don't you think you might have had
a bit too much to drink, sir?
128:
Haaah! Too much? No way, I feel
GREAT! Top of the world, really!
130:
It's New Year's! The kami are kind
enough to overlook the antics of one
single drunk, don't you think?
133:
Sir, this is a shrine. You can't behave
like this in the presence of the kami!
137:
They will not tolerate such boorish
and unbecoming behavior in their
holy shrine!
143:
I understand that you want to
celebrate New Year's, and it's true
that forms of alcohol, such as
O-toso sake, are served during this
time, but—
146:
Okay, Trista, maybe we don't need
ALL the details here.
151:
R-right. Anyway, what I'm trying to
say is that drinking too much is bad
for your body! You should stop for
the day.
157:
Oh... Heh... You might just be right,
little lass. My bad!
159:
No, it's all right. I apologize for raising
my voice like that as well...
164:
Thank you so much for your help
resolving that situation. We get
many of his kind during this time of
year, unfortunately.
165:
But we also get many obedient, kind
visitors, such as yourself. We would
do best to count our blessings!
167:
Though you are not from these
lands, it is clear you have studied
our customs well. I'm sure the kami
are delighted at your presence.
168:
Please, enjoy the rest of your visit.
Farewell.
171:
Well, you certainly salvaged that
situation excellently!
175:
N-no, it was nothing. I merely
applied some of the knowledge I
gained from the books I read...
179:
Let's forget about all of that and
enjoy our visit!
184: Hmm... What should I wish for?
188:
I'm going to wish for new
opportunities to study and gain
more knowledge.
192:
Not to make a name for yourself as
an adventurer, or anything like that?
195:
No, that's something only my effort
alone will determine.
197:
I'm going to do everything I can this
year to reach that goal! I can't wait
to go adventuring with you all as
well.
200:
I see. That's a great goal.
And the same goes for me. We're
counting on you this year, Trista!
